22/11/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina -- BiH on Saturday (November 21st) marked 14 years since the signing of the Dayton Peace Accord which put an end to the 1992-1995 conflict in the country.
The agreement was signed at US military base Wright Patterson near Dayton, Ohio.
It was reached through the mediation of US envoy Richard Holbrooke and was initialled by former Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic, Croatian President Franjo Tudjman and BiH's Alija Izetbegovic.
The official signing ceremony of the document was held in Paris on December 14th.
(B92, RTRS, Srna - 21/11/09)
